addAdmin(address).details: The Owner can add an additional admin

addDeveloper(address,uint256).details: require reward to be even and everything to add up to 100%

params.developer: is address of the developer you wish to add
params.reward: is the percentual weight dev should have of total contract value

checkBalance().details: Checks current balance of contract in oppose to depositAmount.Good to have an overview and see how much money the contract contains at the moment.

constructor.details: Constructor function. The deployer of the contract(msg.sender) will become the owner and get the admin role as well.

extendDeadline().details: Extend the deadline. Will prolong Step 4, implying one cannot make this call after Step 3.*

killContract().details: Option to kill contract for any reason. Not necessary, but if owner for any reason want to erase everything, he should be able to do it.*

numberOfDevs().details: purpose for increased transparency and reflect contract state.

pauseContract().details: Emergency stop which is necessary to have if the owner has technical issues etc.Can only be called by owner or added admin*

params.adminAddress: is the address of the developer you wish to remove.

removeSingleDev(address,uint256).details: Remove single dev from list. Can only be done if contract hasn't yet started, or is paused (it should be a big step to remove someone and it must be communicated properly, why it's necessary to pause to whole operation first).If the contract has started and the admin removes a developer, the weight doesn't need to add up to 100% in order to resume contract. Maybe a replacement isn't necessary and the other developers shouldn't per se get the removed developer's cut.

params.devAddress: is the address of the developer you wish to remove.
params.devInList: is its place in developersList, which need to match. Used as a control mechanism.

resumeContract().details: Resume the contract after it has been paused.Added "hasStarted" as an extra security parameter, otherwise one could start the contract from here instead of startWork().*

startWork(uint256).details: need to transfer value at this step, which will be the value of your project.Developers need to be inserted before start, and the total weight (reward) for devs must be 100% of contract's amount.

stepAccept().details: Owner accepts step when necessary and stepCount will increase by one (stepCount +1).

withdrawal().details: Developers use this to take out money. 1/4 of their weight can be withdrawed for each accepted step.
